<figure class='article-image'></figure>

<div class="article-info"><a class="byline" href="/people/seth-fiegerman/"><img alt="Seth-fiegerman-headshot-cropped" class="author_image" src="http://rack.3.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDEzLzA2LzI1L2QwL1NldGhGaWVnZXJtLmY5NWM5LmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTkweDkwIwplCWpwZw/75555139/ff9/Seth-Fiegerman-headshot-cropped.jpg" /><div class="author_and_date"><span class="author_name">By Seth Fiegerman</span><time datetime="Sat, 10 Aug 2013 21:39:13 +0000">2013-08-10 21:39:13 UTC</time></div></a></div>

</header>
<section class='article-content'>

<div class="shift-to-hero"><p><iframe allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0" height="360" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/zh2ULhXtqYU" width="640"></iframe></p></div>
<p>Drive-in theaters haven't disappeared from American soil, yet, but many of the smaller ones may go dark in the coming months.</p>
<p>Hollywood is expected to stop making celluloid prints that work on traditional 35mm projectors. To continue showing movies, drive-ins will need to cough up tens of thousands of dollars to make the switch to digital projectors — no small feat for businesses in a long-struggling industry. In response, one major car company has decided to help out.</p>
<div class="see-also"><p>See also: <a href="http://mashable.com/2013/07/15/honda-vine-campaign/" data-crackerjax="#post-slider">Honda Responds to Customer Tweets With Real-Time Vine Videos</a></p></div>
<p>Honda is launching a nationwide campaign called Project Drive-In to raise awareness for the plight of drive-ins, and to raise money to help at least five theater owners switch to digital. Honda unveiled a <a href="http://projectdrivein.com/" target="_blank">new website</a> dedicated to the campaign, and is letting people vote on which drive-ins should receive assistance, from now through Sept. 9.</p>
<p><img src="http://rack.1.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDEzLzA4LzEwLzYxL0hvbmRhZHJpdmVpLmIxYjYyLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTEyMDB4OTYwMD4/3bab517d/ddf/Honda-drive-ins-640x366.jpg" alt="Honda drive-ins" class="" data-width="640" data-fragment="m!82eb" data-image="http://rack.1.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDEzLzA4LzEwLzYxL0hvbmRhZHJpdmVpLmIxYjYyLmpwZwpwCXRodW1iCTEyMDB4OTYwMD4/3bab517d/ddf/Honda-drive-ins-640x366.jpg" data-micro="1"></p>
<p>As part of the campaign, Honda is also encouraging people to donate to the Honda drive-in fund,  and to watch at least one movie at their local drive-in. </p>
<p>What do you think of Honda's campaign? Sound off in the comments, below. </p>
<p><em>Image: Flickr, <a href="http://www.mvrealstuff.com/" target="_blank">Jack Pearce</a></em></p>



</section>
